<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6259] Scheduled thread pools is not removed from JMX when shutting down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6259</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example if a route use the aggragate eip with a completion timeout, then the scheduled thread pool is enlisted in JMX. But not removed when the route is removed. Though as fail-safe we always remove the JMX when camel is stopping.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But for people doing dynamic add/remove routes this can become a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
